  "description": "IPv4 CIDR-block algebra modelled on Python's stdlib `ipaddress` module: containsAddr/networkAddr/broadcast/supernet plus collapse (collapse_addresses), specced as full-domain coverage + subset-soundness + no-containment minimality, anchored on frozen Nat mask arithmetic. The `collapse` obligation set is deep: beyond coverage/minimality it pins canonical-form fixpoint, sublist soundness, pairwise disjointness + partition, closure-operator laws (extensive/monotone/idempotent), measure conservation, the no-sibling-merge negative characterisation, the trailing/dominator input-absorption laws, and a battery of normalisation-commutation laws (prefix/suffix-collapse idempotence, idempotent pre-pruning, interior subsumed-block + interior dominator absorption, coverage union homomorphism + append-commutativity, block-set order-independence) whose proofs hinge on a hidden covering-power-preservation invariant (collapsing a list leaves `coveredBy e` unchanged for every block `e`), discovered via a prefix-length-descending surviving-witness argument. Scope: `collapse` models the contained-network-removal + dedup HALF of `ipaddress.collapse_addresses` — it drops every block subsumed by a less-specific block and removes duplicates (the maximal-block, non-subsumed canonical form) but does NOT perform adjacent-sibling coalescing (it does NOT merge `0.0.0.0/25`+`0.0.0.128/25` into `0.0.0.0/24`). `supernet` is the one-level parent (no prefixlen_diff/new_prefix arguments).",
